The Peoples Democratic Party, presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar has described Governor Nyesom Wike as the Jagaban of the party. Atiku said he holds Wike in high esteem, stressing that he is a man of revolution. He disclosed this through the spokesperson of his presidential campaign, Segun Sowunmi, on Arise Television. He stressed that the Rivers State governor is a straightforward person who says things as they are. Also Read: Ortom: 14 Out Of 17 Members Of PDP Panel Preferred Wike As VP Candidate “Wike is our own Jagaban; how do you explain a governor being able to keep other governors in line? One thing you can’t deny him is that he has the ability to say it as it is. He will not bend or colour things. “Atiku holds Wike in high esteem, time and space may not bring them together, but he does. Wike is a man of revolution; he is one of the totems of PDP,” he said.